Introduction

Im Yoonah is a South Korean singer-songwriter, rapper, and actress under SM Entertainment. She is best known as one of the lead rappers and lead dancers, the visual, and the center of the girl group Girls' Generation. She is also a member of it's sub-unit Girls' Generation - Oh!GG.

She debuted as a member of Girls's Generation in August 2007, which went on to become one of the best-selling artists in South Korea and one of South Korea's most popular girl groups worldwide.

Yoona debuted in Girls' Generation's sub-unit "Oh!GG" on September 5, 2018.
